; trust-decay.form — presence-confidence that fades smoothly as a peer goes
; silent, and is restored by a fresh beat.
;
; THE ASK:
;   heartbeat.fk answers liveness with a single cliff: at the threshold edge a
;   cell flips from alive to stale in one tick. A mesh wants a softer reading —
;   a peer that has been quiet a little while is not the same as one long gone.
;   So: model presence-confidence as a budget of GRACE that the silence spends,
;   read it as a hard trust verdict AND a coarse three-band depth, and let a new
;   beat refill the budget. A body that goes quiet fades from the mesh smoothly,
;   not abruptly; a body that beats is whole again.
;
; THE SHAPE  (runnable: form-stdlib/trust-decay.fk · proven: tests/trust-decay-band.fk -> 127)
;
;   A cell's presence is a budget of `max` ticks of grace, started fresh at its
;   last heartbeat `last-beat`. As the observer's clock `now` advances, grace is
;   spent. The whole reading turns on two edges drawn from last-beat:
;       half-edge = (add last-beat half)    — the coarse midpoint of the budget
;       full-edge = (add last-beat max)     — where the budget runs out
;
;   td-beat (max) -> max
;     a fresh beat refills grace to full — it returns the budget a new last-beat
;     carries. The restore half of "decays without a beat, restored by a beat".
;
;   td-trusted? (last-beat now max) -> 1/0
;     1 iff now has not yet reached the full-edge: (ge (add last-beat max) now).
;     At now = full-edge the budget is exactly spent and the verdict is 0. The
;     trust verdict IS this single gate.
;
;   td-faded? (last-beat now max) -> 1/0
;     the exact inverse of td-trusted? — grace fully spent.
;
;   td-confidence (last-beat now max) -> 1/0
;     the still-trusted reading, == td-trusted?. The kernel set has no `sub`, so
;     confidence is the proven-gate form (within budget / decayed), not a curve;
;     the coarse "how deep into the budget" lives in the band below.
;
;   td-grace-band (last-beat now max half) -> "fresh" | "fading" | "gone"
;     two nested `ge` gates layered on the half-edge then the full-edge:
;       within half-edge            -> "fresh"  (the beat is recent)
;       past half-edge, within full -> "fading" (grace draining, still trusted)
;       past full-edge              -> "gone"   (grace spent)
;
; WHY THIS COMPOSES ONTO THE SPINE:
;   heartbeat.fk holds the liveness TABLE; trust-decay.fk is the smoother
;   reading over ONE of its entries. Feed (heartbeat-entry-last-seen entry) as
;   last-beat and the SAME observer clock as now, and the two recipes read the
;   same silence at different resolution: heartbeat's (heartbeat-alive? …
;   threshold) gives the hard yes/no at one edge; td-grace-band gives the coarse
;   fresh/fading/gone arc across the budget. No new clock, no new state — the
;   observer's `now` decides in both, the same trust shape: a cell that drops
;   off the wire silently fades as `now` advances past its refilled edge; a cell
;   that beats refills.
;
;   The decay is read by COMPARING now against the refilled edge
;   (add last-beat max), never by subtracting elapsed ticks — the primitive set
;   has no `sub`, and counting-up-to-an-edge is the honest division-free shape
;   the toolkit uses everywhere (heartbeat's hb-fresh?, the proven-count gates
;   in self-grounding-classifier.fk). The three-band return is the nested
;   string-classifier shape from sg-authority — one reading, three kernels, the
;   same word out.
;
; KIN — the body already holds each piece; this composes them into smooth decay:
;   heartbeat.fk (the liveness table this reads one entry of; last-seen ->
;   last-beat) · self-grounding-classifier.fk's sg-authority (the nested-`if`
;   string-band shape) · the proven-count / edge-gate discipline (no float, no
;   sub — gate on an integer edge) · the three-way validate.sh (no trusted
;   prover — Go=Rust=TS agreeing IS the proof; this band locks at 127).
;
; ONE HONEST LANE:
;   this is a COARSE presence-confidence reading, not a probability and not a
;   continuous decay curve. It answers "is this peer still within its grace
;   budget, and roughly how deep into it?" in integers the three kernels compare
;   exactly. The trust verdict is binary (within budget / decayed); the depth is
;   three bands, not a percentage. No asserted confidence, no elapsed-tick
;   arithmetic the kernel set cannot carry — only an edge the observer's clock
;   crosses, read identically by every sibling.
